screen.screenDetails: Silver Bullets is a library of small molecules that have been shown to promote crystal lattice formation. Each reagent is a mixture of small molecules or macromolecular digest in 0.02 M HEPES sodium pH 6.8 buffer. Each solution contains between 2 and 20 small molecules.
screen.screenReference: Searching for silver bullets: An alternative strategy for crystallizing macromolecules. Alexander McPherson and Bob Cudney. Journal of Structural Biology 156 (2006) 387-406.
